<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2017_01">

<p>Hail! Prosperity! While the 4th year opposite to this <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>itaṉ</foreign></supplied> 4th year of king <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kō</foreign></supplied> Māṟañcaṭaiyaṉ is current <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>cellā niṟka</foreign></supplied>; for bathing <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āṭṭa</foreign></supplied> with milk and ghee <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>pālum neyyum</foreign></supplied> Bhaṭāra of Tirukkiḻkōṭṭam in Tirukkuṭamukku, king Māṟañcaṭaiyar gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kuṭutta</foreign></supplied> hundred and thirty-eight cows <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>pacu</foreign></supplied>; <supplied reason="subaudible">he</supplied> gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kuṭutta</foreign></supplied> hundred <foreign>kācu </foreign>for burning <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>erikka</foreign></supplied> two perpetual lamps; with these cows <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>i-ppacuviṉ-āl</foreign></supplied>, everyday, ten <foreign>nāḻi </foreign>of milk and <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> of ghee <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>; with these <foreign>kācu </foreign><supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>i-kkāciṉ-āl</foreign></supplied>, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></p></div>

